  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study was intended to assess the value of a hemostatic and sealing agent, a collagen
      sponge coated with human coagulation factors (fibrinogen and thrombin) (TachoSil速), for
      decreasing occurrence of seroma after axillary lymphadenectomy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
